{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LH56nPuBezJUXc6E8SAB5M","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01CA6BMQFjEUnHxztkAsLH8N","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n ray create configmap config-audit --from-literal=findings.txt=\"$(cat <<'AUDIT_EOF'\nRAY CLUSTER CONFIGURATION AUDIT\nNamespace : ray\nAudit date: 2026-06-24\nAuditor   : read-only inspection (no live resources modified)\n\n================================================================\n1. WORKER REPLICA COUNT\n================================================================\nResource     : deployment/ray-worker\nCurrent      : 3 replicas (3/3 Ready)\nBaseline     : 2 replicas (from last-applied annotation on the Deployment)\nDeviation    : +1 replica — worker pool was scaled up after initial apply.\n               deployment.kubernetes.io/revision is \"1\" (pod template unchanged)\n               but spec.replicas was patched from 2 → 3.\n\n================================================================\n2. IMAGE VERSIONS\n================================================================\ndeployment/ray-head   : rayproject/ray:2.9.0\ndeployment/ray-worker : rayproject/ray:2.9.0\n\nBoth deployments are on the same image tag. The change-plan ConfigMap\n(see section 5) documents rayproject/ray:2.9.0 as the post-upgrade version\nand lists a future upgrade path to 2.10.0.\n\n================================================================\n3. RESOURCE REQUESTS / LIMITS\n================================================================\ndeployment/ray-head   resources: {} (none defined)\ndeployment/ray-worker resources: {} (none defined)\n\nCPU scheduling behaviour (from container command args):\n  ray-head  : --num-cpus=0  (head is excluded from task scheduling)\n  ray-worker: --num-cpus=1  (each worker advertises 1 schedulable CPU)\n\nCOMPLIANCE RISK: No Kubernetes resource requests or limits are set on either\ndeployment. Without requests, the scheduler cannot make informed placement\ndecisions; without limits, a runaway process can exhaust node memory and\ntrigger OOM evictions of other workloads. See recommendations (section 7).\n\n================================================================\n4. EXPOSED SERVICES\n================================================================\nService    : ray-head\nType       : ClusterIP  (10.96.112.176)\nNo external-IP / NodePort / LoadBalancer / Ingress defined.\n\nPorts:\n  gcs        6379/TCP  → Ray GCS (node-connect / client endpoint)\n  dashboard  8265/TCP  → Ray Dashboard\n\nDEVIATION — Dashboard port:\n  The last-applied Service annotation has only port gcs:6379. The live Service\n  also exposes dashboard:8265 — this port was added after the initial apply.\n\nDEVIATION — Dashboard process flag:\n  The original ray-head pod template (from last-applied annotation) ran:\n    ray start ... --include-dashboard=false\n  The live pod template (Deployment revision 2) runs:\n    ray start ... --include-dashboard=true --dashboard-host=0.0.0.0\n  The dashboard is now running and bound to all interfaces inside the pod.\n  It is reachable cluster-internally at http://10.96.112.176:8265 but is NOT\n  exposed outside the cluster (ClusterIP only — no NodePort or Ingress).\n\n================================================================\n5. ACTIVE CONFIGMAPS\n================================================================\nName              Keys       Age    Notes\n----------------  ---------  -----  ----------------------------------------\nkube-root-ca.crt  ca.crt     28 min System-managed; default in every namespace\nchange-plan       plan.md    ~1 min Migration/change plan document (see below)\nray-job-script    job.py     16 min Job runner script (modified from original)\n\nchange-plan / plan.md content summary:\n  A structured migration plan for the next upgrade window. Documents the\n  current state (replicas=3, image=2.9.0, dashboard exposed) and proposes:\n  (a) image upgrade to 2.10.0, (b) adding CPU/memory resource bounds,\n  (c) scaling workers to 5, (d) optional NodePort for dashboard (gated on\n  security review). The plan is marked READ-ONLY and contains no live changes.\n\nray-job-script / job.py deviation:\n  The last-applied annotation shows the original script as:\n    ray.init(address=\"ray://ray-head:10001\") / print(\"pong\") / ray.shutdown()\n  The live script is substantially different: it calls subprocess ray stop/start\n  explicitly, resolves the pod IP via socket.gethostbyname, and connects via\n  address=\"ray-head:6379\" (GCS port) rather than the client port 10001.\n  This script is referenced by the ray-client pod but does not alter cluster\n  configuration itself.\n\n================================================================\n6. RUNNING PODS (non-deployment)\n================================================================\npod/curl-test   : Running, age ~18 min — appears to be an ad-hoc connectivity\n                  test pod; not managed by a Deployment or ReplicaSet.\npod/ray-client  : Running, age ~2 min — likely a one-shot job pod referencing\n                  the ray-job-script ConfigMap above.\n\nNeither pod was created by a controller; they will not restart on failure.\nNeither is part of the Ray cluster itself (head or worker roles).\n\n================================================================\n7. COMPLIANCE NOTES AND RECOMMENDATIONS\n================================================================\nISSUE-1 [HIGH] No resource requests or limits on ray-head / ray-worker.\n  Risk    : Node-level OOM evictions; poor scheduling placement; noisy-neighbour\n            CPU contention.\n  Action  : Set CPU and memory requests+limits before the next change window.\n            Starting values suggested in change-plan ConfigMap:\n              ray-head   — request 500m CPU / 1Gi mem; limit 1000m / 2Gi\n              ray-worker — request 500m CPU / 1Gi mem; limit 2000m / 4Gi\n\nISSUE-2 [MEDIUM] Ray Dashboard exposed on all pod interfaces (0.0.0.0:8265).\n  Risk    : Any pod in the cluster can reach the dashboard without authentication.\n            Ray Dashboard has historically had no built-in auth.\n  Action  : Either restrict to loopback (--dashboard-host=127.0.0.1) and require\n            kubectl port-forward for operator access, or add a network policy\n            limiting ingress to port 8265 to specific namespaces/principals.\n            If NodePort exposure is approved (change-plan section 2d), a security\n            review is mandatory first.\n\nISSUE-3 [LOW] Orphaned ad-hoc pods (curl-test, ray-client) not managed by a\n  controller.\n  Risk    : These pods are invisible to the Deployment reconciler; if evicted they\n            will not restart. Their presence may indicate unfinished manual tests.\n  Action  : Remove after confirming they are no longer needed.\n\nISSUE-4 [LOW] ray-job-script ConfigMap content diverges from last-applied.\n  Risk    : The annotation represents stale desired state; a re-apply from the\n            original manifest would overwrite the live script silently.\n  Action  : If the modified script is intentional, re-apply (kubectl apply)\n            the updated manifest to bring the annotation in sync.\n\nAUDIT CONCLUSION\nThe cluster is operational with 1 head + 3 workers, all on rayproject/ray:2.9.0.\nThree non-default changes are confirmed versus the initial apply: worker replicas\nscaled from 2→3, dashboard enabled with --include-dashboard=true, and dashboard\nport 8265 added to the Service. No resource bounds are defined on any workload\n(highest-priority gap before next change window). No live resources were modified\nduring this audit.\nAUDIT_EOF\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Create config-audit ConfigMap with audit findings"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5527,"cache_read_input_tokens":30097,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5527},"output_tokens":39,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dc02510d-bc43-4535-b408-26e796008627","uuid":"1d8fdaf2-3de8-44aa-9d43-84bc8a63f1e3","request_id":"req_011CcMcuEsVbVvZ6Ttg8v4f2"}
